    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="527"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d527">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Moscow Embassy Files: Lot F–96</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs of the Soviet
                        Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Molotov</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the American Ambassador in the Soviet
                        Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Standley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-22">August 22,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Ambassador</hi>: Please inform the President of the
                    following reply of the Chairman of the Soviet of People’s Commissars of the
                    USSR, I. V. Stalin, to the message of the President, received August 19: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I have received your message of August 19. I also regret that you could
                            not have participated in the conversations which I recently had with Mr.
                            Churchill.</p>
                        <p>In connection with your remarks regarding the shipment from the United
                            States during the month of August of tanks and war materials, <pb
                                facs="0638" n="632" xml:id="pg_632"/> I would like to emphasize our
                            special interest at the present time in receiving from the United States
                            aircraft and other types of armaments, and also trucks, in the greatest
                            possible quantity. Furthermore, I hope that all measures will be taken
                            to guarantee the most expeditious delivery of goods to the Soviet Union,
                            especially by the northern sea route.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>V. <hi rend="smallcaps">Molotov</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
